eam\n|-\n! 2002\n| Women's Table Tennis national team\n|-\n! 2003\n| [[Luxembourg Davis Cup team]]\n|-\n! 2004\n| [[Luxembourg Davis Cup team]]\n|-\n! 2005\n| [[Guy Rosen]] together with [[Viktoriya Fadina]] (Dance)\n|-\n! 2006\n| [[Luxembourg Davis Cup team]]\n|-\n! 2007\n| [[Luxembourg national football team]]\n|-\n! 2008\n| [[Luxembourg national football team]]\n|-\n! 2009\n| Women's Table Tennis national team\n|-\n! 2010\n| [[Handball Esch]]\n|-\n! 2011\n| [[Luxembourg national football team]]\n|-\n! 2012\n| [[F91 Dudelange]]\n|-\n! 2013\n| [[Handball Esch]]\n|-\n! 2014\n| Luxembourg Women's Table Tennis\n|-\n! 2015\n| Luxembourg Women's Table Tennis\n|-\n! 2016\n| Luxembourg Women's Table Tennis\n|-\n! 2017\n| [[Luxembourg national football team]]\n|-\n! 2018\n| [[F91 Dudelange]]\n|-\n! 2019\n| [[F91 Dudelange]]\n|}\n\n==Individual statistics==\n\n===Winners of more than three titles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=150 colspan=2| Name\n! width=150| Sport\n! width=100| Titles\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#FFC0CB\"|\n| [[Jeanny Dom]]\n| [[Table tennis]]\n| 7\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#6495ED\"|\n| [[Marc Girardelli]]\n| [[Skiing]]\n| 6\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#6495ED\"|\n| [[Nancy Kemp-Arendt]]\n| [[Swimming (sport)|Swimming]], [[triathlon]]\n| 6\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#6495ED\"|\n| [[Kim Kirchen]]\n| [[Bicycle racing|Cycling]]\n| 6\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#6495ED\"|\n| [[Christine Majerus]]\n| [[Bicycle racing|Cycling]]\n| 6\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#FFC0CB\"|\n| [[Roland Bombardella]]\n| [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]]\n| 4\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#FFC0CB\"|\n| [[Charly Gaul]]\n| [[Bicycle racing|Cycling]]\n| 4\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#FFC0CB\"|\n| [[Carine Risch]]\n| [[Table tennis]]\n| 4\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#FFC0CB\"|\n| [[Charles Sowa]]\n| [[Racewalking|Walking]]\n| 4\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#FFC0CB\"|\n| [[Elizabeth May (athlete)|Elizabeth May]]\n| [[Triathlon]]\n| 4\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#FFC0CB\"|\n| [[Gilles Muller]]\n| [[Tennis]]\n| 4\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#6495ED\"|\n| [[Sylvie H\u00fclsemann]]\n| [[Water skiing]]\n| 3\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#6495ED\"|\n| [[Dani\u00e8le Kaber]]\n| [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]]\n| 3\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#6495ED\"|\n| [[Anne Kremer]]\n| [[Tennis]]\n| 3\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#6495ED\"|\n| [[Andy Schleck]]\n| [[Bicycle racing|Cycling]]\n| 3\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#6495ED\"|\n| [[Marie Muller]]\n| [[Judo]]\n| 3\n|}\n\n===Titles by sport===\nNot including team of the year award.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=150| Sport\n! width=100| Sportspersons\n! width=100| Titles\n|-\n| [[Bicycle racing|Cycling]]\n| 8\n| 24\n|-\n| [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]]\n| 9\n| 16\n|-\n| [[Table tennis]]\n| 4\n| 13\n|-\n| [[Triathlon]]\n| 4\n| 8\n|-\n| [[Tennis]]\n| 4\n| 9\n|-\n| [[Football (soccer)|Football]]\n| 4\n| 7\n|-\n| [[Skiing]]\n| 1\n| 6\n|-\n| [[Archery]]\n| 3\n| 4\n|-\n|| [[Racewalking|Walking]]\n| 1\n| 4\n|-\n| [[Fencing (sport)|Fencing]]\n| 3\n| 3\n|-\n| [[Water skiing]]\n| 1\n| 3\n|-\n| [[Powerlifting|Weightlifting]]\n| 1\n| 3\n|-\n| [[swimming (sport)|Swimming]]\n| 2\n| 3\n|-\n| [[Karate]]\n| 3\n| 3\n|-\n| [[Judo]]\n| 1\n| 3\n|-\n| colspan=3|<small>Note: [[Nancy Kemp-Arendt]]'s first two titles are categorised under swimming, and most recent three under triathlon.</small>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.sportspress.lu/trophees/ Website]\n\n{{Luxembourgish Sportspeople of the Year}}\n{{National Sportsperson of the Year}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Luxembourgish Sportspeople Of The Year}}\n[[Category:National sportsperson-of-the-year trophies and awards|Lux]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian awards|Sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian sportspeople| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of Luxembourgian people|Sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 1954]]\n[[Category:1954 establishments in Luxembourg]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\nThe '''Sportsperson of the Year''' awards are a group of awards awarded to the most popular [[Luxembourg]]ish sportsperson of the preceding year. There are two main categories: one for men ({{lang-fr|Troph\u00e9e du Meilleur Sportif}}), and one for women (''Troph\u00e9e de la Meilleure Sportive''). Other awards are given for the best team (''Challenge de la Meilleure Equipe''), best young sportsperson (''Prix du Jeune Espoir''), most honorable sportsperson (''Prix d'Honneur''), and for fair play (''Prix du Fair play''). The current holders of the main awards are [[Bob Bertemes]] and [[Christine Majerus]], while the team award is held by [[F91 Dudelange]].\n\n==List of winners==\n\n===1954\u20131965===\nFrom 1954 until 1965, there was a single title of \"Sportsperson of the Year\", awarded to either a male or female sportsperson.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=40| Year\n! width=150| Winner\n! width=150| Sport\n|-\n! 1954\n| [[Charly Gaul]]\n| [[Bicycle racing|Cycling]]\n|-\n! 1955\n| [[Charly Gaul]]\n| [[Bicycle racing|Cycling]]\n|-\n! 1956\n| [[Charly Gaul]]\n| [[Bicycle racing|Cycling]]\n|-\n! 1957\n| [[Josy Stoffel]]\n| [[Gymnastics]]\n|-\n! 1958\n| [[Charly Gaul]]\n| [[Bicycle racing|Cycling]]\n|-\n! 1959\n| [[Jean Link]]\n| [[Fencing (sport)|Fencing]]\n|-\n! 1960\n| [[Josy Stoffel]]\n| [[Gymnastics]]\n|-\n! 1961\n| [[Sylvie H\u00fclsemann]]\n| [[Water skiing]]\n|-\n! 1962\n| [[Norbert Haupert]]\n| [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]]\n|-\n! 1963\n| [[Norbert Haupert]]\n| [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]]\n|-\n! 1964\n| [[Charles Sowa]]\n| [[Racewalking|Walking]]\n|-\n! 1965\n| [[Ren\u00e9 Kilburg]]\n| [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]]\n|}\n\n===1966 onwards===\nIt was decided to divide the contest into two from 1966, with separate categories for men and for women, as it has remained since.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=40 rowspan=2| Year\n! colspan=2| Sportsman of the Year\n! colspan=2| Sportswoman of